name: Panax_longe-petiolatus
reference: Prodr. [A. P. de Candolle] 4: 253. 1830 [late Sep 1830] (as longe-petiolatum)
remarks: “longe” is an adverb (not an adjective); in the epithet longe-petiolatus (= longly petioled), the two words can stand independently, and the hyphen is permitted
